{"name": "acscend", "metadata": {"name": "ACSCeND", "version": "1.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/SML-CompBio/ACSCEND", "license": "MIT License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pandas", "numpy", "torch", "scikit-learn", "joblib", "scipy"], "summary": "A deep learning tool for bulk RNA-seq deconvolution and Stem Cells Sub-Class prediction.", "upload_time": 1733223742}, "documentation": ["# AI-based Cancer Stem Cell profiler and Neoplasia Deconvoluter (ACSCeND)\r\n\r\n**ACSCeND** is a Python package designed to analyze and process stem cell transcriptomics data. It includes two core modules for predicting stem cell subtypes and deconvoluting bulk RNA-seq data using deep learning.\r\n\r\n## Features\r\n\r\n1. **Stem Cell Subtypes Predictor**  \r\n   Identify stem cell subtypes \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Pluripotent, Multipotent, or Unipotent \u00e2\u20ac\u201d from single-cell stem cell transcriptomics data.\r\n\r\n2. **Deep Learning-based Deconvoluter**  \r\n   Deconvolute bulk RNA-seq data into meaningful components using cutting-edge deep learning techniques.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Installation\r\n\r\nInstall ACSCeND using pip:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npip install ACSCeND\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Documentation\r\n\r\nComprehensive documentation is available at:  \r\n[ACSCeND Documentation](https://acscend.readthedocs.io/en/latest/)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Usage\r\n\r\n### Stem Cell Subtypes Predictor\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom ACSCeND import Predictor\r\n\r\n# Example usage\r\npredictor = Predictor()\r\nsubtypes = predictor(input_data)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Deep Learning-based Deconvoluter\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom ACSCeND import Deconvoluter\r\n\r\n# Example usage\r\nreal_freq, real_gep = Deconvoluter(pseudo_data, sig_matrix, pseudo_freq, real_data, normalized=False)\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor detailed examples and API reference, visit the [documentation](https://acscend.readthedocs.io/en/latest/).\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Suggestions\r\n\r\nWe welcome suggestions! If you have any ideas or feedback to improve ACSCeND, please reach out to [Shreyansh Priyadarshi](mailto:shreyansh.priyadarshi02@gmail.com).\r\n\r\n---\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ACSCeND.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ACSCeND.utils.compute_ccc", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "y_true", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y_pred", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Compute Concordance Correlation Coefficient (CCC)"]}, {"name": "ACSCeND.utils.compute_rmse", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "y_true", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y_pred", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Compute Root Mean Square Error (RMSE)"]}, {"name": "ACSCeND.utils.raw_to_cpm", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "df", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ACSCeND.utils.load_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "freq", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "org", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "normalized", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ACSCeND", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "ACSCeND.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ACSCeND.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "ACSCeND.Deconvoluter", "xref": {"fqname": "ACSCeND.acscend.Deconvoluter", "project": null}}, {"name": "ACSCeND.Predictor", "xref": {"fqname": "ACSCeND.acscend.Predictor", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "ACSCeND.model", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "ACSCeND.model.AttentionBlock", "bases": ["nn.Module"], "methods": [{"name": "ACSCeND.model.AttentionBlock.__init__", "asynchronous": false, 